---
title: "Guardrails: Work Queue Claim with Safety Checks"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Agent
    participant C as Coordinator
    participant G as Guardrails + Policy

    A->>C: get_work(task_types=["implementation"])
    C->>C: claim_task (atomic PL/pgSQL)
    C->>G: check_operation(task description)
    G->>G: Pattern match against destructive ops
    G->>G: Check agent trust level

    alt No violations — safe to proceed
        G-->>C: safe=true, allowed=true
        C->>C: audit_log(task_claimed)
        C-->>A: Task dispatched
        A->>A: Execute implementation
    else Destructive op detected — blocked
        G-->>C: safe=false (e.g. "DROP TABLE")
        Note over G: min_trust=3, agent_trust=2 → BLOCKED
        C->>C: Release task back to queue
        C->>C: audit_log(guardrail_block)
        C-->>A: Blocked (insufficient trust level)
    end
